        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Cerebrotendinous xanthomatosis (CTX) is an anomaly of bile acid synthesis characterized by neonatal cholestasis childhood-onset cataract adolescent to young adult-onset tendon xanthomata and brain xanthomata with adult-onset neurologic dysfunction."
        },
